review_blob:
0,5 l bottle @Szekesfehervar - Spajz
Pours opal orange/bloody colour with a finger white head. Leaves decent lacing.
Aroma is medium full with honey , grassy/hay hop.
Taste coming with malty sweetness, some bitter caramel and smooth pepper. Leaves alcoholic notes at the end.
Full bodied, really Enjoyed!

Bottle - Clearbrown color. Medium, frothy head. Herbal and grassy aroma with distinct sour yeasty notes and light sulphurous, resinous feel. Crisp grassy hops initially, Moderate sweet molasses, caramel and liquorice mouthfeel leading to crisp herbal, slightly roasted bitternes. Light to medium bodied.

Bottle - Beige cream head. Opaque, near black body. Sweet and roasted malt aroma with prunes and dark bread. Sweet dark bread is dominating the flavor as well. A caramel note and suggestions of dark dried fruits. Hops not included. Alcohol well masked. Almost full-bodied. Sweet malty ending
Bottle - Light nutty aroma with toffee, malts and berries. Brown, beige head, good lace. Nutty, malty, quite hoppy w/ Citra?!. Medium body. Flavourful, easy going.

Bottle - Dark simcoe whore.  Aroma is simcoe, some roasty malt. Flavour is flat caramel cardboardy malt with some simcoe at first, followed by the to be expected roast and nice simcoe hop bitterness and flavour. Loved it!

Bottle (2012) - Darkest brown with small town ring of head. Christmas spice aroma, lots of clove, slightly perfumed and floral. Taste is rich malty, cocoa, clove, toffee mad molasses. Medium bodied with a clean finish.
beer_name: Anchor Our Special Ale (2005 and later)

review_blob: Bottle - Pours a hazy, pale gold, with a firm white head. Fruity aroma, a bit of yeast and sweat, citrusy hop notes, caramel and mango. Dry, light to medium bodied, medium bitterness with a lot of carbon. Fruity, malty taste, a hint of grain, citrus peel, hops and apple.

Bottle / on -tap - Unfiltered hazy, light golden coloured beer with a thin, white head. The aroma is fruity and hoppy (Magnum and Spalt!?). Herbal taste along with a sweet malt base. Leave a really awesome bitterness in your mouth. Currently the best bottom fermented here in Hungary.

On tap - Well, well, wont be my favourite but pretty decent one. Deep hazy black with very dark brown small head, leaving small lacing. Aroma is full: roasted malts, caramel, coffee hint of dark choco. 
Taste was smooth, full bodied beast, alcohol is well hidden.
Highly concentrated stuff.

On tap - Hazy deep golden colour with small decent white head, l eaves nice lacing. Fruity/citrus US hops with a delicious malty base. Flavour is nicely balanced, very decent APA. Malty body and lots of fruity bitterness. Could drink all day long.

Bottle -  Cloudy light golden beer with a very strong white head. The aroma is quite sour, floral and bitter, and the flavour is very bitter and sour with a large amount of hoppyness and grassyness. Lot of carbon within, could be fuller bodied. Overall a reasonable sour and bitter beer but was expecting a bit more. Unusual US beer.
beer_name: Flying Dog In de Wildeman Farmhouse IPA

review_blob: Bottle -  Pours clear golden with a huge creamy white head. Aroma is honey, grassy hops and malt.. Taste is good malty, moderate sweet caramel with a decent grassy hop with a really nice bitter end. Decent stuff :)
Bottle- Deep golden body with an off-white head. Grainy, hoppy aroma. Notable hoppyness in the taste with some maltyness. Not bad but nothing extra.
Can -  Pours clear yellow with a medium white head. The aroma is corn, malt and some fruity hops. The flavour is quite grainy and light malty.

Bottle-  Pours clear deep ruby brown with a nice beige creamy head leaving lacing. Aroma is sweet, malty, slightly yeasty, spicy, dark fruits and brown sugar. Flavor is sweet, fullbodied, spicy, cloves, yeasty, apricots, malty and has a nice bitterness. Finishes sweet malty, spicy and a bit bitter.
beer_name: Gouden Carolus Cuvee Van De Keizer Blauw/Blue

review_blob:
Bottle - Bottle. Pours an opaque honey color with a really nice, frothy white head. Aroma of herbs, a touch of fig, and alcohol. Tingles the tongue going down. Medium bodied. Finishes okay. Has a little bit of an alcoholic burn on the back end. 
If you feel vine type characters you probably consumed it too cold.

Can - Mild haze on golden-amber colour w/ mid white head. Light citric wheat aroma , bit plain underdeveloped, grainy malty finish.
Light/watery bodied. Soft ,silky character. Straight forward weizen.

Can - Hazy dark brown colour w/ creamy beige head Citric smell for the nose.. The beer starts sharp followed by a sweet-tart tasted aroma ruled by citrus some chocolate notes and wheat. It finishes tart and refreshing escorted by dark chocolate, citrusses and spices. Enjoyable brew.
Bottle- Golden pale colour with average white head. Far malty and corny aroma. Light sweetness and lightly bitter. Average carbonation, quick dry finish. Normal.
Bottle - Pours deep beige, nearly black. Artificial for the nose and in taste as well. This a syrup and not really a beer.
Bottle - Pours deep beige, nearly black. Artificial for the nose and in taste as well. This a syrup and not really a beer.
Bottle @Hungary- Clear yellow pour with a white head. Skunky, bready aroma. Skunky taste with a bitter (notes only) aftertaste.

Bottle - Nice amber coloured, small off-white head which goes away . Good for the nose:hoppy & fruity. Taste comes with medium maltiness followed with tons of hop aromas: pine and grapefruit. Alcohol notes well hidden,a bit dry finish. Enjoyed very much!

Bottle - Clear amber color, huge creamy white head, caramel and fruits (raisins, citrus, cherries) aroma, coriander and yeast notes, sweet honey flavor, metallic notes, medium body, slighty alcoholic finish with spices and some hops.

Bottle - Thin head goes away quickly, leaving no lace at all. Sourish yeast and fruity to the nose. Rich & dry maltiness with a tons of plum and red fruits with a hint of vinegar. Body is really creamy.
Bottle - Moderat malty aroma. Large, frothy, white head. Good lacing. Clear yellow body. Light sweet flavor. Medium palate.

On tap @ Fozdefeszt - Just wow! A decent IPA with hefe yeast ?! Medium white foam sitting on a hazy orange/copper beer, full of citrus/grapefruit followed with an Ok pine as well. Definitely want to drink it again!

Bottle - Pours a nice amber color with a large dense off-white/tan head. Aroma of sweet malt, biscuits, and light grassy hops. Flavor matches aroma with light bitterness -too light for me - at the finish..

Can - There is a DEFINITE between the Czech and the Hungarian Kozel. Sadly, the non checz ones are trash. So the original one:
Clear golden in colour with a medium head. Taste comes with the usual bohemian grassy / bready /cripsy flavour although this one is not that sweet like the rest. There is an Ok bitterness within.

Bottle - Clear, golden colour with a thick foamy white head. Grassy hopp with a moderately sweet malty background. Slightly bitter flavour, light to medium bodied with a crispy mouthfeel. Sourish yeast is all way around. Pale malt character with a tinge of cara-malty; slightly buttery taste with a rising grassy and herbal hops profile towards the moderately bitter finish.

Bottle- Pours clear golden amber, medium white head and light lacing. Aroma is grapefruit and citrus hops, light pine, dusty grains. Taste quite hoppy for such low ABV, tongue tingling, profile much like the nose, mild sweetness towards the end before nice bitter finish, dry. Light sparkling body, this one goes down quick and easy. Really tasty stuff, awesome session brew.!

Bottle - . Dark golden colored beer, with a white good sized head. Floral aroma, lightly malty along with exotic fruits. Fruity taste with pine, caramel and grass. Very good bitter ending, taste of grapefruit stays
On tap @Fozdefeszt early 2012 - Small head with yellow body. Tons of unnatural pear aroma and unfermented sugars(?) To tell the truth it was hardly drinkable.. :(

Bottle -Poured dark red nearly brown, with a thin head. Aroma has some lovely chocolate notes, also some coffee in there and roasted malt. Flavor is roasted malt, dark chocolate and almonds. Suprisingly light bodied, but very nice lasting finish of chocolate. Very drinkable!
Canned - Golden lager with a thin white head. Aroma of fresh malts and nice hopping. In mouth, a very mineral lager with light sweet malt notes and some honey in the aftertaste. Too watery.

Bottle - Pours deep burnt copper. This is definitely the most beautiful head Ive ever seen on a beer.  Aroma is of floral, piney, resinous, citrus hops with a huge burst of caramel and toffee, as well as a huge fresh grainy smell. It almost smells like unfermented sweet wort. Taste is sugary sweet and intensely bitter, with huge wallops of malt and hops throughout. Low carbonation makes it a very drinkable stuff.
Want more barleywine for sure :)

Bottle- A colabrown beer with a almost medium and beige head. Aroma is balanced, basicly roasted and chocolate, also some sweetness and ryebread. Taste is roasted, ryebread, black coffee, some herbs, not totally dry, some sweet malts. Medium- bodied, nice drinkability. Succesfully, light stout, quite complex and not too roasted.

Bottle - Aroma is full of hops, pines, oats herbs and spices. A faint fruity smell is lightly present in the background. Appearance is a copper/gold with a huge foam head. Taste is an immediate punch to the throat of pure hoppy bitterness with a malty background. Very delightful complex flavors with a heavily bodied bitter finish. Overall, this is a incredibly refreshing and perfectly bitter beer. A must for hop fanatics!
beer_name: Flying Dog Double Dog Double Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle-  Clear deep golden, medium white head. Grainy, slightly earthy malt aroma with some floral hops. Light to meidum bodied, medium carbonation. Dry with slightly minerally bitterness.

Bottle - Golden in colour, leaves nice lacing. Malty for the nose.  The sweetness and the bitterness just as balanced as in a typical Czech pilsener. A bit watery but still pretty decent. Bravo and recommended!

Bottle - WoW! This beer should definitely rate higher!
Really nice orange/golden in colour with a big white had which leaves decent lacing. Taste begins with malt sweetness, followed with a thin yeasty sourness and some biscuit. Ends with good amount of hop, which is unusual for a Belgian ale but absolutely good that this one has it. Great beer!

Bottle - (1,5L PET)
Golden - hazy orange in color with a small tan head. Complex beer: taste comes with the malts sweetness and a note of the yeast, late bitterness. Honey is present in the aftertaste. Could be a little bit more balanced but to tell the truth Ive liked it this way.
Bottle - Deep amber in color with thin white head. Taste is sweet with a hint of smoke. Not really bitter, but liked it.
Bottle - Deep red colour, thin white head. Aromas of cherrys, alcohol, caramel and chocolate. Taste is cherry and port-wine like. A little bit of chocolate perhaps. Finish is long and sweet.

Bottle- Poured a cloudy brown color ale with an off-white foamy head with good retention and some lacing. Aroma of candi sugar and nice rich Belgian style malt is quite enjoyable. Taste is also a nice enough mix between candi sugar with some notes rich sweet Belgian malt and light dry figs. Body is full with limited filtration and great carbonation with no apparent alcohol.

Bottle- Dark amber/brown color; Medium slightly creamy body. 
Aroma of malt, caramel, & some hop. Flavor of slight roasted malt, hops, caramel, toffee, and light fruit; Finish is slightly bitter which I pretty enjoyed.

Bottle - An amber coloured beer with two-fingered, white, frothy head that mostly diminishing. The aroma is brutal hoppy, its like orange, flowers, pine and resin. The taste is bitter with notes of grapefruit. The finish is long and dry hoppy bitterness. Oily texture and medium body.
beer_name: Flying Dog Snake Dog IPA (2008 and later)

review_blob: Bottle - Pours a wonderful yellow, slightly hazy colour with a huge, long lasting and frothy head. aroma is yeast, spicy and citric hops, some notes of pear and pepper as well. smells absolutely fantastic! medium body, light bitter mash-up of citric and spicy notes. pleasent long aftertaste. really refreshing, also because of the quite fizzy carbonation. Could drink it all day long...

Bottle - Pours a deep gold with an enormous head that retains wonderfully. Perfect look. Smells of yeast, pineapple, and grassy hops. I love this taste. This is the type of beer that I crave. Nice mellow hoppy bitterness, with no bad aftertaste. Nice and creamy smooth. Beautiful and tasty. Recommend.

Bottle - Tasted a while ago, however really liked it. Golden, orangy in color with a nice head. This unfiltered hefe comes with the usual line: banana and orange, some yeasty flavour. After taste is a bit citrusy.
